{"id":14880935,"mediaExerciseId":"a8c6df91-a8d4-416e-91a2-068202b1e967","exerciseName":"9","chapterName":"6","chapterTitle":"Discounted Cash Flow Valuation","groupId":612300,"groupTitle":"Critical Thinking Questions","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":183,"solutions":[{"id":5968032,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this exercise, we will identify if there should be any objections to subsidized and unsubsidized loans.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":60,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/30/8bf28639561496d657263d5a5652bb8d/c9c336268d1f2233a6d2d8e48e2c5e83/lateximg_large.png","width":1001},"regular":{"height":31,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/30/8bf28639561496d657263d5a5652bb8d/c9c336268d1f2233a6d2d8e48e2c5e83/lateximg.png","width":500}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"Subsidized loans are student loans that the government subsidizes; these loans do not accrue interest until the student graduates.\n\n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":66,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/30/8bf28639561496d657263d5a5652bb8d/083760bc38d38f304d1b662468f3ca81/lateximg_large.png","width":995},"regular":{"height":34,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/30/8bf28639561496d657263d5a5652bb8d/083760bc38d38f304d1b662468f3ca81/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"In contrast to subsidized loans, Unsubsidized loans are student loans that the government does not provide support. Unsubsidized loans immediately accrue interest upon disbursements.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":103,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/30/8bf28639561496d657263d5a5652bb8d/58cd2b52fb2ccde7bfd83c849a316686/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":53,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/30/8bf28639561496d657263d5a5652bb8d/58cd2b52fb2ccde7bfd83c849a316686/lateximg.png","width":499}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"**There are no objections to both subsidized and unsubsidized loans**\n\nBoth loans provide financial alternatives for students, the subsidized loans funded by the government being granted only to students with financial needs. Although both loans repayment obligations are not extinguished, subsidized loans have a relatively lower interest as the interest does not accrue until the student graduates.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":218,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/30/8bf28639561496d657263d5a5652bb8d/976459f9db83ff09e8273fdc03646ad8/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":110,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/30/8bf28639561496d657263d5a5652bb8d/976459f9db83ff09e8273fdc03646ad8/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4}],"rating":5,"solutionUuid":"57ed33d6-2e7c-4ce5-aacf-8a1d36d16345","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":4},{"id":6361863,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"We need to determine if existence of two types of student loans are fair.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"First, let's establish what two types of loans are present.\n\nFirst, there is a **subsidized loan** is a type of loan where **interest is shouldered by the lender for some time**. \n\nIn case of student loans, government pays interest until student finishes studies, whereupon the interest starts to add up on top of the loan amount, and now this interest and loan amount have to be paid from students income.\n\nSecond is **unsubsidized loan**, where the **interest and later payout are covered by borrower alone**, student in this case.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"The immediate and obvious point of contention is that **unsubsidized loan places very heavy economic and mental pressure of the borrower**, as the student is forced to pay to interest while keeping up with the studies, which necessitates the finding of part-time/full-time job during studies or borrowing from someone else to cover this.\n\nThis is the main objection that can be levied against two types of loans.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3}],"rating":0,"solutionUuid":"644ee8dd-c833-4c20-aef1-ca014e176c62","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":3}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14880936,"exerciseName":"10","page":183,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"06e014cf-0c75-41be-a892-f6da400c84f5","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-6-critical-thinking-questions-10-06e014cf-0c75-41be-a892-f6da400c84f5"},{"id":14880937,"exerciseName":